---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../styles/home.css';
---

<BaseLayout title="PicFast — Self-hosted Image Hosting Platform">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none">
          <path d="M2 7L5.5 10.5L12 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        </svg>
        Open Source · GNU GPL v3
      </div>
      <h1>Self-hosted image hosting,<br />deployed in one command.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        A complete image hosting platform, launched with a single <code>make docker-up</code>.
        Features a full admin panel, 6 storage backends, and an API-first architecture.
        Natively integrates with AI agents via MCP, ShareX for quick captures, and any HTTP client.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-code">
        <div class="code-label">
          <span class="dot red"></span>
          <span class="dot yellow"></span>
          <span class="dot green"></span>
          <span class="code-filename">terminal</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code><span class="prompt">$</span> git clone https://github.com/atbeta/picfast.git
<span class="prompt">$</span> cd picfast
<span class="prompt">$</span> cp .env.example .env
<span class="prompt">$</span> make docker-up</code></pre>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/docs/getting-started" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/atbeta/picfast" class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor">
            <path d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.013 8.013 0 0016 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z"/>
          </svg>
          View on GitHub
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="features">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Everything you need, one command away</h2>
      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 22 22" fill="none">
              <rect x="2" y="3" width="18" height="16" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75"/>
              <path d="M7 10h8M7 14h5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <rect x="4" y="2" width="6" height="4" rx="1" fill="currentColor"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>One-Command Deploy</h3>
          <p>Clone, configure, run <code>make docker-up</code> — the full stack starts in one go. PostgreSQL, the application, and Mailpit launch together. Prebuilt images on Docker Hub make production deployment equally straightforward.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 22 22" fill="none">
              <rect x="3" y="3" width="16" height="16" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75"/>
              <path d="M3 8h16M7 8v11" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <rect x="7" y="1" width="8" height="3" rx="1" fill="currentColor"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Full Admin Panel</h3>
          <p>Manage users, groups, storage strategies, images, and site configuration from a clean React dashboard. Day-to-day operations require no direct database access.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 22 22" fill="none">
              <rect x="2" y="4" width="18" height="14" rx="2.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75"/>
              <path d="M2 8l6 4 4-3 8 5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              <circle cx="7" cy="7" r="1.5" fill="currentColor"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>API-First, AI-Ready</h3>
          <p>Clean REST API with an OpenAPI spec and live documentation. The built-in MCP server enables Claude, Cursor, and other AI agents to upload, list, and manage images. Run <code>npx @picfast/mcp</code> to connect.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 22 22" fill="none">
              <path d="M11 2L3 6v6c0 5.25 3.4 10.15 8 11.4 4.6-1.25 8-6.15 8-11.4V6L11 2z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              <path d="M7 10l3 3 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Native Tool Integrations</h3>
          <p>One-click ShareX setup via a dedicated config endpoint. Multi-format output — URL, Markdown, BBCode, HTML. Works with curl, Python, JavaScript, or any HTTP client. No vendor lock-in.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 22 22" fill="none">
              <path d="M4 4h14v14H4z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              <path d="M4 8h14M8 8v10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>6 Storage Backends</h3>
          <p>Local filesystem, S3-compatible (MinIO, R2), Alibaba OSS, Tencent COS, Qiniu Kodo, and WebDAV. Switch backends anytime — existing images stay where they are.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 22 22" fill="none">
              <path d="M11 3v4M11 15v4M3 11H7M15 11h4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <circle cx="11" cy="11" r="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Image Processing & Safety</h3>
          <p>Automatic thumbnail generation, configurable compression, and watermark support. Optional content moderation with an admin approval queue.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="comparison">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">How it compares</h2>
      <div class="table-wrapper">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th></th><th>Chevereto</th><th>Photoview</th><th>Self-built S3</th><th>PicFast</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Setup time</td><td>~30 min</td><td>~20 min</td><td>~2 hours</td><td><strong>~5 min</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Admin panel</td><td>Basic</td><td>Limited</td><td>None</td><td><strong>Full React dashboard</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>API support</td><td>Basic</td><td>Limited</td><td>Custom</td><td><strong>OpenAPI + live docs</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>ShareX integration</td><td>✅</td><td>❌</td><td>Custom</td><td><strong>✅ Built-in</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>AI / MCP tools</td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td><strong>✅ 5 tools + resources</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Storage backends</td><td>Limited</td><td>Local only</td><td>S3 only</td><td><strong>6 backends</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Content moderation</td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>Custom</td><td><strong>✅ Built-in</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Image processing</td><td>Basic</td><td>Limited</td><td>Custom</td><td><strong>✅ Compression + watermark</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>License</td><td>Paid</td><td>MIT</td><td>N/A</td><td><strong>GPL v3</strong></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="quick-start">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Quick start</h2>
      <div class="quick-start-grid">
        <div class="qs-step">
          <div class="qs-num">1</div>
          <div class="qs-content">
            <h3>Clone and configure</h3>
            <p>Clone the repo, copy the example config files, and adjust to your needs.</p>
            <div class="hero-code small"><pre><code>git clone https://github.com/atbeta/picfast.git
cd picfast
cp .env.example .env
cp config.example.yaml config.yaml
$EDITOR config.yaml</code></pre></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="qs-step">
          <div class="qs-num">2</div>
          <div class="qs-content">
            <h3>Start everything</h3>
            <p>One command launches PostgreSQL, Mailpit (local email testing), and the application.</p>
            <div class="hero-code small"><pre><code>make docker-up</code></pre></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="qs-step">
          <div class="qs-num">3</div>
          <div class="qs-content">
            <h3>Upload your first image</h3>
            <p>Register a user, obtain a token, and upload via curl — or use the web UI, ShareX, or MCP.</p>
            <div class="hero-code small"><pre><code>curl -X POST http://localhost:18080/api/v1/auth/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '&#123;"email":"you@example.com","password":"hunter2","name":"You"&#125;'

curl -X POST http://localhost:18080/api/v1/images \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" \
  -F "file=@image.png"</code></pre></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="qs-cta"><a href="/docs/getting-started" class="btn btn-primary">Full documentation &rarr;</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
